{{ infobox person | name = José Cabanis | image=José Cabanis 1962.jpg | caption = José Cabanis in 1962 | birth_date = {{birth date|1922|3|2|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Toulouse]], France | death_date = {{death date and age|2000|10|6|1922|3|2|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Balma]], France | nationality = French | occupation = Novelist | known for = Member of the [[Académie française]] }}
'''José Cabanis''' (2 March 1922 – 6 October 2000) was a French novelist, essayist, historian and magistrate. He was elected mainteneur of the [[Académie des Jeux floraux]] in 1965 and a member of the [[Académie française]] in 1990.
