'''Minaret Khaje Alam''' belongs to the [[Timurid Empire]] and is located at Hatef street in [[Isfahan]]. This relic was recorded in Iran’s National Hertage on 6 January 1932.<ref>[https://www.britannica.com/place/Iran/The-Timurids-and-Turkmen#ref315853 The Timurids and Turkmen]</ref><ref>[https://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/timu/hd_timu.htm The Art of the Timurid Period (ca. 1370–1507)]</ref>
