'''Raymond Arroyo''' (born September 25, 1970) is a [[New York Times]] bestselling author,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/series/WIL/will-wilder|title=Will Wilder|website=PenguinRandomhouse.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref> journalist and a producer. He is the news director and lead anchor of EWTN News, the news division of the [[EWTN|Eternal Word Television Network]]. He is creator and host of the news magazine ''The World Over Live'' seen in more than 350 million households around the globe and heard on 500 AM/FM affiliates throughout the US. Arroyo is also author of the best-selling Will Wilder series (Random House/Crown) for young readers.
==Early life== Arroyo was born in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]].<ref name="americawillwilderandthe">{{cite news|last1=Salai|first1=Sean|title=‘Will Wilder and the Relic of Perilous Falls’: Author Q&A with Raymond Arroyo|url=http://www.americamagazine.org/content/all-things/will-wilder-and-relic-perilous-falls-author-qa-raymond-arroyo|accessdate=October 29, 2016|work=[[America (Jesuit magazine)|America]]|date=March 16, 2016}}</ref> He graduated from the [[Tisch School of the Arts]] at [[New York University]].<ref name="americawillwilderandthe"/>
==Career== Arroyo worked at the [[Associated Press]], the ''[[New York Observer]]'', and for the political columnist team of [[Evans and Novak]].
Arroyo's biography of EWTN's founder, [[Mother Angelica]], was a New York Times bestseller, as were each of his following books. He is also the editor of ''Mother Angelica's Little Book of Life Lessons and Everyday Spirituality ''([[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]), "Mother Angelica's Private and Pithy Lessons from the Scriptures" (Doubleday), "The Prayers and Personal Devotions of Mother Angelica" (Doubleday), co-author of, "Of Thee I Zing: America's Cultural Decline from Muffin Tops to Body Shots" ([[Threshold Editions]]) and a series of children's books; "Will Wilder: The Relic of Perilous Falls" and "Will Wilder: The Lost Staff of Wonders" ([[Random House]]/[[Crown Publishing Group|Crown]]). His writings have been published by ''[[Newsweek]]'', ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', ''[[The Washington Times]]'', ''[[Financial Times|The Financial Times]]'', and ''[[National Catholic Register]]''.
=== Broadcasting === Arroyo is best known as host of the EWTN news program ''The World Over Live'', where he routinely interviews leading figures of the day including the first and, to this date, only English language conversation ever recorded with [[Cardinal (Catholicism)|Cardinal]] [[Joseph Ratzinger]], who would later become [[Pope Benedict XVI]]. Other interviews include [[Mel Gibson]], on the set of his film ''[[The Passion of the Christ]]'', presidential candidates, [[Plácido Domingo|Placido Domingo]], and [[Supreme court|Supreme Court]] justices. He has been featured on ''[[Today (NBC program)|The Today Show]]'', ''[[Good Morning America]]'', and ''[[Access Hollywood]]'', "The O'Reilly Factor", "Erin Burnett Out Front", "CNN Headline News”, and other television shows.
Arroyo is a frequent guest and occasional substitute host of ''[[The Laura Ingraham Show]]'' on radio<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/laura-ingraham-was-trump-before-trump-but-is-she-made-for-tv/2017/10/24/d1481916-b50e-11e7-9e58-e6288544af98_story.html|title=Laura Ingraham was ‘Trump before Trump.’ But is she made for TV?|last=Thompson|first=Krissah|date=2017-10-25|work=Washington Post|access-date=2018-02-07|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediaite.com/tv/hannity-awkwardly-compares-laura-ingraham-to-bill-oreilly-she-calls-it-a-low-blow/|title=Hannity Awkwardly Compares Laura Ingraham to Bill O’Reilly, She Calls It a ‘Low Blow!’|website=www.mediaite.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref> and ''[[The Ingraham Angle]]'' on [[Fox News]] television.
==Personal life== Arroyo resides in [[Northern Virginia]] with his wife Rebecca and their three children.<ref name="americawillwilderandthe"/>
